<subSubSection id="F9AAF8E20731FFC52DF9EC8F790CFBD6" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B10FAB690731FFC52DF9EC8F7DE3FCA6" blockId="56.[151,1436,654,1326]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52DF9EC8F7D17FD13" bold="true" box="[199,321,690,715]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Species in this genus are characterized by (1) frontoparietals, 1–2, (2) supraciliaries, 3–4, (3) supraoculars, three (rarely four), (4) prefrontal contact, absent (or contact sometimes in 
<taxonomicName id="76B0D0EA0731FFC52949ECEB79C4FD36" baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[1143,1426,726,750]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Aspronema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dorsivittatum">
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52949ECEB79C4FD36" box="[1143,1426,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Aspronema dorsivittatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (5) parietal contact, present, (6) rows of nuchals, 0–2, (7) dorsals + ventrals, 111–132, (8) total digital lamellae, 185–193, (9) a dark middorsal stripe, present, (10) dark dorsolateral stripes, present, (11) dark lateral stripe, present, and (12) dark ventral striping, absent. Maximum body sizes in this genus are 
<quantity id="7648068C0731FFC52961ED7F788EFC82" box="[1119,1240,834,858]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="8.4" metricValueMin="7.6" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="80.0" valueMax="84.0" valueMin="76.0">76–84 mm</quantity>
SVL (
<bibRefCitation id="D521D6980731FFC5281AED7F7D6CFCA6" author="Vrcibradic &amp; Rocha" firstAuthor="Vrcibradic" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="813 - 825" refId="ref179327" refString="Vrcibradic, D. &amp; Rocha, C. F. D. (2011) An overview of female reproductive traits in South American Mabuya (Squamata, Scincidae), with emphasis on brood size and its correlates. Journal of Natural History, 45, 813 - 825." type="journal article" year="2011">
Vrcibradic &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="7374658B0731FFC52D8AED5B7CADFCA6" box="[180,251,870,894]" country="Uruguay" name="Rocha" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Rocha</collectingRegion>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<tableCitation id="FC329ED20731FFC52C6FED5B7DFEFCA6" box="[337,424,870,894]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="29.[151,241,690,714]" captionText="TABLE 2. Taxonomic summary for lizards of the Subfamily Mabuyinae. For each genus, the number of species, occurrence on islands, and sample size, are shown along with the primary diagnostic characters used in distinguishing the genera. See individual accounts for additional diagnostic characters specific to each genus. Sample size is listed separately (in parentheses) for total lamellae. Sample size indicates specimens examined, except for Orosaura and Exila where data are from the literature (see accounts). N = no, Y = yes. Rare or uncommon states given in parentheses." pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B10FAB690731FFC52DF9EDB77EE6FC32" blockId="56.[151,1436,654,1326]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
The combination of three supraoculars and a narrow, dark middorsal stripe distinguishes this genus from all others. Also, while pale dorsolateral and ventrolateral stripes are not rare in 
<taxonomicName id="76B0D0EA0731FFC52ED1ED937839FC1E" authorityName="Mittleman" authorityYear="1952" box="[1007,1135,942,966]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Mabuyinae">Mabuyinae</taxonomicName>
, those stripes in species of the Genus 
<taxonomicName id="76B0D0EA0731FFC52C30EDEE7DDBFC33" authorityName="Hedges &amp; Conn" authorityYear="2012" box="[270,397,979,1003]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Aspronema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52C30EDEE7DDBFC33" box="[270,397,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Aspronema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are especially distinctive.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B10FAB690731FFC52DF9EDCB790CFBD6" blockId="56.[151,1436,654,1326]" box="[199,1370,1014,1039]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52DF9EDCB7D78FBD7" bold="true" box="[199,302,1014,1039]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" reason="1">Content.</emphasis>
Two species are placed in this genus: 
<taxonomicName id="76B0D0EA0731FFC52FE5EDCB7FAAFBD6" baseAuthorityName="Dunn" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[731,1020,1014,1038]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Aspronema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cochabambae">
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52FE5EDCB7FAAFBD6" box="[731,1020,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Aspronema cochabambae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="76B0D0EA0731FFC5290CEDCB78B1FBD6" baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[1074,1255,1014,1038]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Aspronema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dorsivittatum">
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC5290CEDCB78B1FBD6" box="[1074,1255,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">A. dorsivittatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="FC329ED20731FFC529CBEDCB791FFBD6" box="[1269,1353,1014,1038]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="22.[151,241,1290,1314]" captionText="TABLE 1. Classification of lizards of the Family Mabuyidae, Subfamily Mabuyinae (61 species). Additional details on distribution are provided in the text." pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F9AAF8E20731FFC52DF9EA277EA2FB8E" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B10FAB690731FFC52DF9EA277EA2FB8E" blockId="56.[151,1436,654,1326]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52DF9EA277D36FBEB" bold="true" box="[199,352,1050,1075]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" reason="1">Distribution.</emphasis>
The genus is distributed in southern South America, from 
<collectingCountry id="C9A7EBF90731FFC5290FEA2778D5FBEA" box="[1073,1155,1050,1074]" name="Bolivia" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and southern 
<collectingCountry id="C9A7EBF90731FFC5280BEA27792FFBEA" box="[1333,1401,1050,1074]" name="Brazil" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Brazil</collectingCountry>
to northern 
<collectingCountry id="C9A7EBF90731FFC52DC2EA037D39FB8E" box="[252,367,1086,1110]" name="Argentina" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="C9A7EBF90731FFC52C44EA027DB5FB8F" box="[378,483,1087,1111]" name="Paraguay" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="C9A7EBF90731FFC52F20EA027ED6FB8F" box="[542,640,1087,1111]" name="Uruguay" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="298BB7EC0731FFC52FB1EA037EB1FB8E" box="[655,743,1086,1110]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1798,1821]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,308,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-88@25.[151,1436,301,1777]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 8. Distribution of the 16 genera of Neotropical skinks, Family Mabuyidae, Subfamily Mabuyinae. (A) Genera occurring in the greater Caribbean region. (B) Genera occurring exclusively in South America. (C) Additional genera occurring in South America, including one with representatives on Caribbean islands." pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F9AAF8E20731FFC52DF9EA5E7DF4FB1B" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B10FAB690731FFC52DF9EA5E7DF4FB1B" blockId="56.[151,1436,654,1326]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52DF9EA5E7D18FBA3" bold="true" box="[199,334,1123,1147]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name (
<taxonomicName id="76B0D0EA0731FFC52F0DEA5E7EE7FBA3" authorityName="Hedges &amp; Conn" authorityYear="2012" box="[563,689,1123,1147]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Aspronema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52F0DEA5E7EE7FBA3" box="[563,689,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Aspronema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is a neuter noun derived from the Greek adjective 
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC5283AEA5E7915FBA2" box="[1284,1347,1123,1146]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">aspro</emphasis>
(white) and noun 
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52C38EABA7D15FB46" box="[262,323,1159,1182]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">nema</emphasis>
(thread), referring to the distinctive narrow and white dorsolateral and ventrolateral stripes present in species of this genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F9AAF8E20731FFC52DF9EAF278C0FAF6" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B10FAB690731FFC52DF9EAF278C0FAF6" blockId="56.[151,1436,654,1326]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52DF9EAF27D6DFB3F" bold="true" box="[199,315,1231,1255]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This pair of species shares a suite of morphological traits and clusters in molecular phylogenies (Mausfeld &amp; Lotters 2001; 
<bibRefCitation id="D521D6980731FFC52CF6EACE7ECCFAD2" author="Harvey" box="[456,666,1266,1291]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Harvey" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="43 - 56" refId="ref172443" refString="Harvey, M. B., Aguayo, R. &amp; Miralles, A. (2008) Redescription and biogeography of Mabuya cochabambae Dunn with comments on Bolivian congeners (Lacertilia: Scincidae). Zootaxa, 1828, 43 - 56." type="journal article" year="2008">
Harvey 
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52F1FEACE7E0FFAD3" box="[545,601,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="D521D6980731FFC52F9BEACF7FD9FAD2" author="Miralles" box="[677,911,1266,1291]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Miralles" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="598 - 616" refId="ref175852" refString="Miralles, A., Rivas, G., Bonillo, C., Schargel, W. E., Barros, T., Garcia-Perez, J. E. &amp; Barrio-Amoros, C. L. (2009 b) Molecular systematics of Caribbean skinks of the genus Mabuya (Reptilia, Scincidae), with descriptions of two new species from Venezuela. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 156, 598 - 616." type="journal article" year="2009" yearSuffix="b">
Miralles 
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52E36EACE7F16FAD3" box="[776,832,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">et al.</emphasis>
2009b
</bibRefCitation>
), including our analysis (
<figureCitation id="298BB7EC0731FFC52999EACF78BDFAD2" box="[1191,1259,1266,1290]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,562,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-175@16.[151,1436,553,1829]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 5 (continued on the next page)" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Palm and sole color is dark in 
<taxonomicName id="76B0D0EA0731FFC52C78EB2B7E31FAF6" baseAuthorityName="Dunn" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[326,615,1302,1326]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Aspronema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cochabambae">
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52C78EB2B7E31FAF6" box="[326,615,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Aspronema cochabambae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and pale in 
<taxonomicName id="76B0D0EA0731FFC52FCEEB2B78C4FAF6" authority="(Harvey et al. 2008)" baseAuthorityName="Harvey" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[752,1170,1302,1326]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Aspronema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dorsivittatum">
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52FCEEB2B7FF3FAF6" box="[752,933,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">A. dorsivittatum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D521D6980731FFC52E8DEB2B78DCFAF6" author="Harvey" box="[947,1162,1302,1326]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Harvey" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="43 - 56" refId="ref172443" refString="Harvey, M. B., Aguayo, R. &amp; Miralles, A. (2008) Redescription and biogeography of Mabuya cochabambae Dunn with comments on Bolivian congeners (Lacertilia: Scincidae). Zootaxa, 1828, 43 - 56." type="journal article" year="2008">
Harvey 
<emphasis id="83C4777B0731FFC52930EB2A7811FAF6" box="[1038,1095,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
